<p>Just to tell you some of their features, the bottom of the gondola is flat to navigate the shallow waters of the Venetian lagoon, which is only a few cm deep; the iron of the gondola head is essential to gain stability by counterbalancing the gondolier&#39;s weight. It is also <strong>amazing to observe the gondoliers going about their jobs</strong>. Small intersections can pose a risk of collision for 2 gondolas.  To get around the problem, when approaching a blind intersection, the gondolier will simply let out a loud whistle. A gondolier, when approaching from another direction but still out of sight, would answer with another whistle. One gondola could then yield the right of way to the other without fear of a collision.</p>

